item.name: Kadhi
item.desc: Kadhi is a popular North Indian dish, featuring a tangy and spiced yogurt based curry. It often includes besan [gram flour] for thickness and is seasoned with mustard seeds, curry leaves, and various spices. Vegetables or pakoras [deep fried fritters] are sometimes added, enhancing the dish flavor and texture.

item.name: Plain Rice
item.desc: Plain rice is a simple and versatile staple, featuring fluffy, cooked grains. With a neutral taste, it complements various dishes, acting as a blank canvas for flavors. Whether served as a side or a base for sauces, its subtle texture and mild essence make it a fundamental component in diverse culinary traditions worldwide.

item.name: Jeera Rice
item.desc: Jeera rice is a fragrant Indian dish made by cooking basmati rice with cumin seeds [jeera] and other aromatic spices. The result is a flavorful and slightly nutty rice dish that pairs well with a variety of Indian curries and gravies.

item.name: Plain Paratha
item.desc: A plain paratha is a unleavened Indian flatbread made from whole wheat flour, water and salt. It is rolled cut into a thin disc, cooked on a hot griddle with ghee or oil until golden brown, resulting in a flaky, layered texture. This versatile bread complements various dishes and can be enjoyed on its own or with accompaniments like yogurt, pickles or chutney.

item.name: 5 Poori
item.desc: Five fluffy poori, perfectly paired with a tangy chutney. An ideal snack to enjoy with your loved ones.

item.name: Aloo Paratha
item.desc: Aloo paratha is a popular Indian flatbread stuffed with spiced mashed potato. The dough is typically made from wheat flour and rolled out, then filled with a mixture of mashed potatoes seasoned with spices like cumin, coriander and garam masala. The stuffed dough is then rolled flat and cooked on a griddle with ghee or oil until golden brown. Aloo paratha is often served with yogurt, pickles and chutney.

item.name: Pyaaz Paratha
item.desc: Pyaaz paratha is a popular Indian flatbread that features a flavorful stuffing of finely chopped onions mixed with various spices. The dough, typically made from whole wheat flour, is rolled out, filled with the seasoned onion mixture and then cooked on a griddle with ghee or oil until golden brown. The result is a delicious and aromatic dish, perfect for breakfast or as a side dish, showcasing the sweet and savory taste of caramelized onions within a soft and flaky paratha.

item.name: Tea
item.desc: Made with milk, tea leaves and sugar boiled to perfect aromatic colour and give you a perfect refreshing feeling.
